<https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/24a88bcd0889b676cb9230fa90ffa7d0> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/ENG>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021002817>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Red Chromatic Index (RCI) also known as Red Chromatic Coordinate (RCC) is a measure of the redness of vegetation. It is calculated from daily averaged RGB (Red, Green, Blue) composites values of digital images captured by PhenoCams.\nLönnstorp Research Station (2024). Phenocam - Red Chromatic Coordinates (RCC) Composite Image Mean Values from SAFE Agroecological Field Experiment, 2022-01-01–2022-12-31 [Data set]. Swedish Infrastructure for Ecosystem Science (SITES). https://hdl.handle.net/11676.1/d1oxoaMiywRN9zgYJB3iX4Wa"@en;
